#Load data
df <- data.frame(read_excel("/Users/jaclynpereira/Desktop/Marketing.xlsx"))

#Drop unnecessary columns
modelData <- subset(df, select=-c(ID, Dt_Customer, Recency, Complain, Z_CostContact, Z_Revenue, Response, NumDealsPurchases, AcceptedCmp2, AcceptedCmp3, AcceptedCmp4, AcceptedCmp5))
#Discretization 
modelData$Education <- as.factor(modelData$Education)
modelData$Marital_Status <- as.factor(modelData$Marital_Status)
modelData$AcceptedCmp1 <- as.factor(modelData$AcceptedCmp1)

#How many missing/NA income values? 24 noted.
nrow(modelData[is.na(modelData$Income),])
## [1] 24
#Sort by education level
modelData <- modelData[order(df$Education),]

#Replaced missing income na's with the average value of income before and after the na's
modelData$Income <- na_interpolation(modelData$Income)

#Validated that missing na's were replaced
nrow(modelData[is.na(modelData$Income),])
## [1] 0

Create test and train data

train_list <- createDataPartition(modelData$Year_Birth, p=0.66, list= FALSE)

trainModel <-modelData[train_list,]
testModel <- modelData[-train_list,]

Bayes

nb=naiveBayes(AcceptedCmp1~., data = trainModel, laplace = 1, na.action = na.pass)

predNB=predict(nb, newdata=testModel, type=c("class"))

confusionMatrix(predNB, testModel$AcceptedCmp1)

#Tuning the new model

model_knn2 <- train(AcceptedCmp1 ~ ., data = KNNcampaign_train1, method = "knn",
                    tuneGrid = data.frame(k = seq(1, 25)),
                    trControl = trainControl(method = "repeatedcv", 
                                             number = 10, repeats = 3))

#SVM Analysis

#Dropping the marriage variable as it has zero variance within the SVM model
svmDataTrain <- subset(trainModel, select=-c(Marital_Status))
svmDataTest <- subset(testModel, select=-c(Marital_Status))

model_svm_rbf <- train(AcceptedCmp1 ~ ., data = svmDataTrain,
                       preProcess = c("center", "scale"),
                       tuneGrid = expand.grid(sigma = seq(0, 1, 0.1),
                                              C = seq(0, 1, 0.1)),
                       method = "svmRadial",
                       trControl = trainControl(method = "boot",
                                                number = 25))

#Remove Outliers
modelData <-modelData[modelData$Year_Birth >1921,]
modelData <-modelData[modelData$Income < 200000,]
modelData <-modelData[modelData$MntMeatProducts < 1000,]
modelData <-modelData[modelData$MntSweetProducts < 200,]
modelData <-modelData[modelData$MntGoldProds < 275,]

#Discretize Data
modelData$Education <- as.factor(modelData$Education)
modelData$Marital_Status <- as.factor(modelData$Marital_Status)
modelData$AcceptedCmp1 <- as.factor(modelData$AcceptedCmp1)
modelData$Year_Birth <- cut(modelData$Year_Birth, breaks = c(0,1950, 1960, 1970, 1980, 1990, Inf), labels = c("1940s", "1950s", "1960s", "1970s", "1980s", "1990s"))
modelData$Income <- cut(modelData$Income, breaks = c(0,25000, 50000, 75000, 100000, Inf), labels = c("VeryLow", "Low", "Medium", "High", "VeryHigh"), include.lowest = TRUE)
modelData$MntWines <- cut(modelData$MntWines, breaks = c(0,50, 300, 700, 1000, Inf), labels = c("VeryLow", "Low", "Medium", "High", "VeryHigh"), include.lowest = TRUE)
modelData$MntFruits <- cut(modelData$MntFruits, breaks = c(0,7, 60, 100, 150, Inf), labels = c("VeryLow", "Low", "Medium", "High", "VeryHigh"), include.lowest = TRUE)
modelData$MntMeatProducts <- cut(modelData$MntMeatProducts, breaks = c(0,50, 100, 300, 500, Inf), labels = c("VeryLow", "Low", "Medium", "High", "VeryHigh"), include.lowest = TRUE)
modelData$MntFishProducts <- cut(modelData$MntFishProducts, breaks = c(0,10, 25, 50, 125, Inf), labels = c("VeryLow", "Low", "Medium", "High", "VeryHigh"), include.lowest = TRUE)

Create test and train data

train_list <- createDataPartition(modelData$Year_Birth, p=0.66, list= FALSE)

trainModel <-modelData[train_list,]
testModel <- modelData[-train_list,]

#decision tree

treeModel<- rpart(AcceptedCmp1~.,trainModel, method="class")
rpart.plot(treeModel, fallen.leaves = FALSE)

predictTree <- predict(treeModel, testModel, type='class')
confusionMatrix(predictTree, testModel$AcceptedCmp1)
